(10383, 1, 'Tanner Tee - Big Base + Hitting Deck Bundle W/ Free Shipping', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Get the Big Base Tanner Tee and the Hitting Deck training mat combined with free shipping.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Big Base provides additional stability and weight.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Please select your stem size.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Item receives free shipping!&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Please note price increase for the adjustable 16-23 inch stem.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tanner Tee Stem Size&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Adjustable 26-43 inch (Adult/Standard)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Adjustable 20-32 inch (Youth/Short)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Adjustable 16-23 inch (Low Ball/Custom Short)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Tanner Tee - Big Base + Hitting Deck Bundle W/ Free Shipping', 'Tanner Tee - Big Base + Hitting Deck Bundle W/ Free Shipping', 'Tanner Tee - Big Base + Hitting Deck Bundle W/ Free Shipping'),
(10380, 1, 'Strider - 12 Sport Balance Bike, Ages 18 Months to 5 Years', '&lt;p&gt;Ryan McFarland, Founder… &quot;The 12 Sport model offers every feature a child (or parent) could want. It is the perfect balance of performance, options, and value, featuring more than 8 years of design evolution and manufacturing improvements.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThis model is similar to the previous ST-4 balance bike, but includes updated graphics and an extra-long seat post.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feature-Rich, Mid-Level Model&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Best Selling Strider Balance Bike&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;For Ages 18 Months to 5 Years Old&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Seat Height Range of 28 - 48 cm (11 - 19 in)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;The perfect starter bike for children 18 months - 5 years&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;No-tool height adjustments for seat and handlebars&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Includes bonus padded seat &amp;amp; XL post for taller riders&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Lightweight design makes it easy for toddlers to control&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Simple, no-tool assembly&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Flat-free tires&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;7 vibrant colors&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Strider?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThrough ten years of development, manufacturing improvements, riding, observation, testing and even racing, Strider Bikes has created a bike that allows for an easy and more successful transition to a pedal bike. Strider specializes specifically in Balance Bikes and in the process the company has developed enhanced features, including the lowest seat in the industry. With Strider’s Four Learn-to-Ride steps, children can jump on a bike and get moving as soon as the bike is set up. As lovers of riding bikes, Strider loves inspiring children to ride. Strider’s mission is to build lightweight, efficient, all-terrain bikes that develop two-wheeled balance, coordination, and confidence. With 1 million sold worldwide, Strider hopes to continue to reach families around the world.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Balance Bikes?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe balance bike is a simple design to teach young children how to steer and balance on two wheels without training wheels. Since the bike has no pedals or other complicated forms of propulsion, most children come to find that riding a balance bike is as easy as walking. Children do not have to fear when they are on a balance bike because they can place their feet solidly on the ground. As the child progresses at his or her pace, they can change to a traditional bicycle whenever they are ready.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Strider 12 Sport&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Feature-Rich, Mid-Level Model offers every feature a child (or parent) could want with custom grips, padded saddle, handlebar pad, and quick release clamps (no-tool adjustment). It is the perfect balance of performance, options, and value. More than eight years of design evolution and manufacturing improvements all packaged into one model. And with a bonus second, taller seat post for the 3-5 year old child, it is the only balance bike a toddler/preschooler will ever need.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Handlebar&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nUnique 12.7mm steel handlebar is 43% smaller than standard to allow better control with tiny hands. Custom logo mini-grips are soft urethane with protective ends. Machined-aluminum quick release allows “No Tools” height adjustment from 46-56cm (18-22”).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Wheel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nStrider-exclusive, ultralight one-piece wheels sport a raised-letter, five-spoke design with 10 bearing support gussets for maximum strength at the lightest weight possible.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nTop-quality sealed cartridge bearings roll smooth and never need adjustment.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Tires&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nEVA polymer (industrial foam) tires are super light and durable yet offer a smooth ride. Best of all, they never need air and will never go flat.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Seat&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSmaller, narrower, and lighter than a typical saddle, our padded seat allows for proper riding position and posture. Includes 2 seatposts for growing children, allowing seat-height adjustments up to 48 cm (19 in).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Bar and seat clamps&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMachined aluminum quick release allows “No Tools” saddle height adjustment from 28-41cm (11-16”) for the perfect fit for your child.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6. Footrest&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nUnique, frame-integrated footrests are properly positioned directly below the saddle for natural bike balance. This position also fosters the advanced ability to stand while gliding as well as pumping and jumping the bike.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7. Brake mount&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nStrider-exclusive rear brake mount allows the addition of a foot-operated brake once the kids are proficiently gliding with feet on the footrests. Brake sold separately.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Strider - 12 Sport Balance Bike, Ages 18 Months to 5 Years', 'Strider - 12 Sport Balance Bike, Ages 18 Months to 5 Years', 'Strider - 12 Sport Balance Bike, Ages 18 Months to 5 Years'),
(10386, 1, 'Strider - Youth 16 Sport No-Pedal Balance Bike, Ages 6 to 10 Years', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&quot;The Strider 16 Sport model is a major redesign of our initial 16&quot; model launched last year. With better components, new features, and more adjustability, we know this bike will be a hit with kids who are just learning to ride for the first time and kids who are dealing with special needs challenges, as well as those who are tearing it up at the skate parks and BMX bike parks. We believe these new models are the perfect balance of simplicity, safety, performance, and FUN, without the weight and complication of pedals,&quot; says Ryan McFarland, CEO of Strider Sports International.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Simple Lightweight Design (8 kg/17.7 lbs)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Max Rider weight - 85 kg/187 lbs&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Available in 5 Vibrant Colors&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Strider?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThrough ten years of development, manufacturing improvements, riding, observation, testing and even racing, Strider Bikes has created a bike that allows for anyone to ride no matter their ability, as well as an easy and more successful transition to a pedal bike. Strider specializes specifically in Balance Bikes and in the process the company has developed enhanced features, including footrests for the rider to use for gliding. With Strider’s Four Learn-to-Ride steps, riders can jump on a bike and get moving as soon as the bike is set up. As lovers of riding bikes, Strider loves inspiring anyone to ride. Strider’s mission is to build lightweight, efficient, all-terrain bikes that develop two-wheeled balance, coordination, and confidence. With 1 million sold worldwide, Strider hopes to continue to reach families around the world.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Balance Bikes?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe balance bike is a simple design to teach anyone at any age how to steer and balance on two wheels without training wheels. Since the bike has no pedals or other complicated forms of propulsion, most riders come to find that riding a balance bike is as easy as walking. Riders do not have to fear when they are on a balance bike because they can place their feet solidly on the ground. As the rider progresses at his or her own pace, they can join in on the excitement of riding a bike with others and even change to a traditional bicycle if they are ready.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Handlebar&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nA low 3 degree sweep highlight these standard 22.2mm, 600mm wide handlebars. Pressed in bearings keep the 1 1/8&quot; stem turning smoothly.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Tires&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe cross terrain tires offer a smooth ride on all surfaces while maintaining traction in the dirt. The tire size is 1.75 - 16 and offer a 42 lb. max psi inflation rating.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Seat&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe fully padded seat is mounted on a rail allowing multiple front to back and seat angle adjustments. A 25.4mm seatpost comes standard on the 16&quot; bike.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Bar and seat clamps&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMachined aluminum quick release allows “No Tools” saddle height adjustment.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Footrest&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nUnique, footrests can be added or removed to adjust to the rider\'s size and ability.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6. Brake mount&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nFrame mounted front and rear v brakes grace the 16&quot; model. These brakes offer greater stopping power compared to a standard caliper style brake.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ASSEMBLY &amp;amp; INFORMATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAll 16” and 20” Sport model Strider Bikes ship partially assembled from the factory and will require final assembly and adjustment by an adult with basic mechanical skills. Please read through the owner’s manual/assembly instructions and watch our assembly video prior to beginning the work (links below). After reviewing the information, if you don’t feel comfortable performing the work, we suggest you have your local bicycle shop perform the work for you.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.striderbikes.com/media/downloads/101620-01.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;User Manual&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.striderbikes.com/media/downloads/Assembly16and20.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Assembly Instructions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/vtdXAW5ptOs?autoplay=1&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Assembly Video&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Strider - Youth 16 Sport No-Pedal Balance Bike, Ages 6 to 10 Years', 'Strider - Youth 16 Sport No-Pedal Balance Bike, Ages 6 to 10 Years', 'Strider - Youth 16 Sport No-Pedal Balance Bike, Ages 6 to 10 Years'),
(10384, 1, 'Amia Chair by Steelcase, 4 Way Adjustable, 14 Colors', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STEELCASE AMIA OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frame and Back Color:&lt;/strong&gt; Black frame, back, and shell&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base Options:&lt;/strong&gt; Base to match frame color&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seat Height:&lt;/strong&gt; Standard seat height, 15.5&quot; - 20.5&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caster Options:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Standard carpet casters&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arms:&lt;/strong&gt; Please select arms option (Yes or No)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upholstery:&lt;/strong&gt; Please select option (14 Colors available)&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AMIA MEANS ERGONOMICS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nBuilt with those a little closer to the ground in mind, the Amia can still adjust its seat pan, arms, and lumbar support height to support a wide range of builds in complete comfort on its plush patented foam cushion.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STEELCASE AMIA SPECS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Weight capacity: 400 lbs.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Seat depth: adjustable between 15.5&quot; and 18.5&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Seat width: 19.375&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Seat height from floor: adjustable between 16&quot; and 21&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Back width: 18.875&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Back height from seat : 25&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Back lumbar height: adjustable between 6.25&quot; and 10&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Lumbar flex zone: 5.25&quot; - 10.25&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Width between arms: adjustable between 15&quot; and 19.5&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Arm to floor: adjustable between 22&quot; and 32.25&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Arm height from seat: adjustable between 7&quot; and 11&quot;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Arm cap pivot range: 30 degrees&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Seat pan angle: -3 degrees to +3 degrees&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Angle between seat and back: 100 degrees to 120 degrees&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Warranty: Limited lifetime&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STEELCASE AMIA FEATURES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sleek Design:&lt;/strong&gt; Gentle arcs keep your space visually uncluttered and your body at its perfect position.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LiveLumbar Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Spring activated back support moves with you all day, no extra adjustments required. No matter how you shift through your shift, it stays on you.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tension Adjustment:&lt;/strong&gt; Keep back support and reclining as mild or as firm as you want it to be.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Armrest Positioning:&lt;/strong&gt; So long as they’re off the dinner table, you can keep your elbows wherever you want them to be with armrests that rise, pivot, expand, and contract however you need them.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seat Pan Adaptability:&lt;/strong&gt; No more cutting off your shin circulation or making your knees do the legwork your posterior was meant to. The seat sliding mechanism will keep the cushion where you need it in relation to your body from the bellybutton down.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ships Assembled:&lt;/strong&gt; The hardest part will be trying not to play in the box.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Amia Chair by Steelcase: Adjustable Back Tension - LiveLumbar Support - Seat Slider - 4 Way Adjustable Arms - Black Frame/Black Fabric, 14 Colors', 'Amia Chair by Steelcase: Adjustable Back Tension - LiveLumbar Support - Seat Slider - 4 Way Adjustable Arms - Black Frame/Black Fabric, 14 Colors', 'Amia Chair by Steelcase: Adjustable Back Tension - LiveLumbar Support - Seat Slider - 4 Way Adjustable Arms - Black Frame/Black Fabric, 14 Colors'),
