(10546, 1, 'ALC Deadman Abrasive Blaster 150-Lb. Capacity', '&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ALC DEADMAN ABRASIVE BLASTER — 150-LB. CAPACITY, MODEL# 40004&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Perfect for surface preparation on any type of irregular surfaces where other forms of preparation such as sanding are difficult&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ideal for removing paint, rust, scale and oxidation on various surfaces&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Steel deadman shutoff handle along with adjustable flow valve and pressure-relieving ball valve provide the operator with complete control of abrasive blasting&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;80–125 psi operating range&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Minimum air volume of 15–25 CFM @ 80 psi&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PRODUCT SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;This ALC® Deadman Abrasive Blaster is perfect for a wide variety of surface preparation jobs such as removing paint, scale, rust and oxidation. Ideal for surface preparation on cars, trucks, machinery, steel, glass etching and much more. Features a 15ft. heavy-duty Goodyear blast hose designed for long life and maneuverability. Durable wheels and built-in handle allow for easy transport. Heavy-duty steel deadman shutoff handle for longevity and safety. Simply add abrasive and hook up to an air supply and you\'re ready to blast. Some assembly required.&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT\'S INCLUDED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;(1) Deadman abrasive blaster&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FEATURES + BENEFITS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Perfect for surface preparation on any type of irregular surfaces where other forms of preparation such as sanding are difficult&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ideal for removing paint, rust, scale and oxidation on various surfaces&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Steel deadman shutoff handle along with adjustable flow valve and pressure-relieving ball valve provide the operator with complete control of abrasive blasting&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;80–125 psi operating range&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Minimum air volume of 15–25 CFM @ 80 psi&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Heavy-duty 15ft. Goodyear blast hose for long life&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;125 psi pressure relief valve for operator safety&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Welded steel frame for strength and durability&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;8in. durable rubber wheels and built-in handle allows for easy maneuverability&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Large ceramic blasting nozzle for longer blast life&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Adjustable abrasive flow valve gives the operator precise control of abrasive mixture when blasting&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Powder-coat finish for superior corrosion resistance&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;1/2in. inside diameter blast hose and 1/2in. ball valves for more powerful abrasive and air flow&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Steel deadman handle shuts off automatically when dropped by use of a rubber sealing block at the nozzle to provide safety to the user&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;1.5 cu. ft. pressure tank holds approximately 150 lbs. of abrasive for longer blasting times&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Abrasive blasting hose features a quick disconnect to easily remove the blasting hose from the unit, making relocating or storage easier&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Built-in funnel and pull up tank closure for faster refills&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Easy-to-read pressure gauge to monitor air pressure&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Recommended for use with a compressor that creates minimum 15 CFM @ 90 psi&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY SPECS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Brand: ALC&lt;/li&